SIMPLE: twentieth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twentieth
<hw>Twen"ti*eth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Twenty</er>; cf. AS. <ets>twentigo⟦edh⟧a</ets>. See
<er>Twenty</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Next in order after the
nineteenth; tenth after the tenth; coming after nineteen others; -- the
ordinal of <xex>twenty</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Constituting, or being, one of twenty equal parts
into which anything is divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twentieth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Twentieth
<hw>Twen"ti*eth</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The next in order
after the nineteenth; one coming after nineteen others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quotient of a unit divided by twenty; one of
twenty equal parts of one whole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twenty</ent>⟦br⟧
